Reference: `100051.html` - Wistom API specification

### LGIN (Login/User Management)
- [x] `login()` - LGIN LGIN/API2: Start session with user credentials
- [ ] LGIN CPWD: Change password
- [ ] LGIN COPW: Change others password
- [ ] LGIN UADD: User add
- [ ] LGIN UDEL: User delete
- [ ] LGIN UINF: User information
- [ ] LGIN SINF: Session info

### SMGR (System Manager)
- [x] `get_smgr_info()` - SMGR INFO: Product info (HW/SW versions, serial numbers, calibration data)
- [x] `get_smgr_network_info()` - SMGR IP##: IP settings (address, subnet, gateway, hostname, MAC, port)
- [x] `get_smgr_serial_settings()` - SMGR SER#: Serial (RS232) settings
- [x] `get_smgr_time()` - SMGR TIME: Date and time
- [x] `get_smgr_temp()` - SMGR TEMP: Temperature (board, sensor, FPGA, configured limits)
- [x] `get_smgr_uptime()` - SMGR UPTI: System running time (uptime, app uptime, load average)
- [x] `get_snmp_agent_listening_port()` - SMGR SCFG: SNMP configuration
- [x] `get_snmp_trap_receivers()` - SMGR SLTR: SNMP list trap receivers
- [ ] SMGR API#: API definition table
- [ ] SMGR CLRD: Clear error dump
- [ ] SMGR DUMP: Error dump
- [ ] SMGR FLSH: Save configuration (SET only)
- [ ] SMGR HIDD: Activate hidden MMI commands
- [ ] SMGR INST: Feature installation (SNMP agent)
- [ ] SMGR LED#: LED status
- [ ] SMGR REST: Restart system (SET only)
- [ ] SMGR SATR: SNMP add trap receiver (SET only)
- [ ] SMGR SDTR: SNMP delete trap receiver (SET only)
- [ ] SMGR VOLT: System voltages and current

### WSNS (WistSense) ✅ COMPLETED
High-level API available via `WistSenseAPI` class in `wistomwsns.py`
- [x] WSNS DATA: Get spectra for debugging - `wsns.get_data()`
- [x] WSNS ENAB: Enable/disable WistSense - `wsns.get_enabled()` / `wsns.set_enabled()`
- [x] WSNS FILT: Software filtering of spectra - `wsns.get_filt()` / `wsns.set_filt()`
- [x] WSNS NEXT: Get current peak frequencies - `wsns.get_next()`
- [x] WSNS PARA: WistSense parameters - `wsns.get_para()` / `wsns.set_para()`
- [x] WSNS PORT: Calibration and sensor ports - `wsns.get_port()`
- [x] WSNS RAWB: Raw spectrum without bias correction - `wsns.get_rawb()`

