## Priority 3: Modbus TCP Implementation

Design from scratch - expose Wistom API data as Modbus holding registers.

- [ ] Create `wistom_modbus_server.py`
- [ ] Define register map (see copilot-instructions.md):
  - [ ] SMGR registers (40000-40999): TEMP, UPTI, TIME, INFO, IP##
  - [ ] WSNS registers (41000-41999): DATA, NEXT
  - [ ] OPM# registers (42000-42999): channel data, spectrum data
- [ ] Implement data type conversions:
  - [ ] FLOAT32 → 2 registers (big-endian IEEE 754)
  - [ ] UINT32 → 2 registers (big-endian)
  - [ ] STRING → N registers (2 ASCII chars per register)
- [ ] Add periodic polling from WistomClient to update registers
- [ ] Add `pymodbus` to requirements.txt

